    <br>
    <br>
    <img src="https://s31606.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/computer-keyboard-emergency-picture-id855364504.jpg" style="float: right;" width="430" height="280">
    <h2 style="font-size: 30px;">Procedures for Reporting Emergencies</h2>
        <p style="line-height: 40px;">In the event of an emergency, individuals should immediately contact the appropriate emergency service by calling the designated phone numbers or using the emergency call boxes located throughout the campus. When reporting an emergency, callers should be prepared to provide the following information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Nature of the emergency</li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Exact location of the incident</li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Any injuries or immediate hazards</li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Their own name and contact information</li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Counseling and Mental Health Services
            </li>
        </ul>   
        <br>
        <br>
    <br> 
    <br>
    <br>
    <img src="https://www.sophe.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/patient-counseling-scaled-2048x1365.jpg" style="float: right;" width="430" height="280">
    <h2 style="font-size: 30px;">University Counseling and Wellness Center:</h2>
        <p style="line-height: 40px;">The university's Counseling and Wellness Center provides a range of mental health services to students, staff, and faculty, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Individual and group counseling</li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Crisis intervention and emergency services</li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Referrals to off-campus mental health providers</li>
            </li>
        </ul>   
        <br>
    <br> 
    <br><br><br>
    <br><br><br><br>
    <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/R.12b1ffa5517850b5ee23ff3e07b2bef7?rik=EFKEjudXXsgdTQ&riu=http%3a%2f%2fwww.systnet.com%2fwp-content%2fuploads%2f2018%2f06%2f20180426.jpg&ehk=k2dGc9MjoRBsbXnrWTicZEGG4vlW7FflK4Dc3K%2bpXjw%3d&risl=&pid=ImgRaw&r=0" style="float: right;" width="430" height="280">
    <h2 style="font-size: 30px;">Access to Services During and After Disasters:</h2>
        <p style="line-height: 40px;">During and after a disaster, the Counseling and Wellness Center offers additional support and resources, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Grief counseling for those who have experienced loss</li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Trauma-informed care and support for individuals affected by the disaster</li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Stress management and coping strategies workshops</li>
            </li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Referrals to community-based mental health and social service providers</li>
        </ul>  
        <br>
    <br>  
    <br> <br><br><br><br>
    <h2 style="font-size: 30px;">Security Protocols</h2>
    <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/R.6aa42aeeab965b874005f64840a3a45e?rik=mvVlbYs8VeF1oQ&riu=http%3a%2f%2fusers.encs.concordia.ca%2f%7edebbabi%2fimages%2finse7100.jpg&ehk=RH11QColhqZrDLcEnpciK%2bjMl%2bL3LKFcKpPs7F5Zppw%3d&risl=&pid=ImgRaw&r=0" style="float: right;" width="430" height="280">
        <p style="line-height: 40px;">The university has implemented a comprehensive set of security measures to ensure the safety and security of the campus community, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Access control systems, such as key cards and biometric scanners, to restrict access to buildings and facilities</li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Surveillance cameras and security patrols to monitor campus activity</li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Emergency communication systems, including panic buttons and mass notification systems, to alert the community in the event of a crisis</li>
            </li>
            <li style="font-size: 13px;">Referrals to community-based mental health and social service providers</li>
        </ul> 
